The article praises the collaboration between SAG-AFTRA and the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers in reaching an agreement through collective bargaining. It highlights the importance of both sides negotiating in good faith to strengthen businesses and provide workers with fair pay and benefits. The article also acknowledges the historic victories achieved by workers in the past three years, resulting in improved pay, benefits, and an economy that benefits everyone. Ultimately, the final decision on the contract will be made by SAG-AFTRA members, but the sacrifices made by workers will lead to a better future for them, their families, and all workers who contribute to creating value.